{
  "info": {
    "name": "TransactionService",
    "_postman_id": "ts-local-tests",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Tests manuels du TransactionService (port 8081 local / 8085 Docker).\n\nArchitecture : TransactionService ne contacte plus KeyService ni l'Orchestrateur.\nIl est appelé PAR l'Orchestrateur avec des données déjà validées.\nToutes les requêtes CRUD fonctionnent dès que la DB est disponible.\n\nPrérequis isolation (sans stack complet) :\n  docker compose up transaction-db\n  ./mvnw spring-boot:run\n\nPrérequis stack complet :\n  docker compose up  (depuis LOG430-Projet2-Infra/)\n\nOrdre recommandé :\n  1. Health\n  2. Saga Simulation → Settle  (stocke transactionId)\n  3. Transactions → GET by ID\n  4. Transactions → POST Create\n  5. Transactions → Réconciliation"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8081",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Port local. Utiliser http://localhost:8085 avec docker compose."
    },
    {
      "key": "transactionId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "participantId",
      "value": "PART-BANK-A-001",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health & Actuator",
      "description": "Endpoints de santé et métriques. Fonctionnent en isolation totale.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Service UP', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('UP');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Info",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/info"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Metrics (liste)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/metrics"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has names array', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('names');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Metrics — JVM memory",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/metrics/jvm.memory.used"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has measurements', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('measurements');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Prometheus (scrape)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/prometheus"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type Prometheus text format', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('text/plain');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Saga Simulation (isolation totale)",
      "description": "Crée une transaction directement en DB et l'amène à un état terminal de façon synchrone.\nAucune dépendance externe — fonctionne sans Kafka, sans Orchestrateur, sans KeyService.\n\nFlows :\n  /settle → CREATED → ACCEPTED → SETTLED\n  /reject → CREATED → REFUSED  → REJECTED\n  /expire → CREATED → EXPIRED\n\nChaque requête stocke l'ID dans {{transactionId}} pour les requêtes suivantes.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Settle : CREATED → ACCEPTED → SETTLED",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/saga/transactions/settle"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Status SETTLED', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('SETTLED');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.id).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', body.id);",
                  "  console.log('transactionId set to', body.id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Reject : CREATED → REFUSED → REJECTED",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/saga/transactions/reject"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Status REJECTED', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('REJECTED');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', body.id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Expire : CREATED → EXPIRED",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/saga/transactions/expire"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Status EXPIRED', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('EXPIRED');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', body.id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Transactions — CRUD",
      "description": "Opérations sur les transactions.\n\nPOST Create simule un appel venant de l'Orchestrateur (clés déjà validées).\nPlus aucune dépendance vers KeyService ou l'Orchestrateur — fonctionne dès que la DB est disponible.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Create Transaction",
          "description": "Simule l'appel de l'Orchestrateur vers TransactionService.\nLes clés sont considérées déjà validées par l'Orchestrateur via KeyService.\nRequiert uniquement la DB (transaction-db).",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"senderKey\": \"KEY-SENDER-001\",\n  \"receiverKey\": \"KEY-RECEIVER-001\",\n  \"amount\": 100.00,\n  \"participantId\": \"{{participantId}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Réponse valide', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body.id).to.match(/^[0-9a-f-]{36}$/i);",
                  "  pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('CREATED');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.senderKey).to.eql('KEY-SENDER-001');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.receiverKey).to.eql('KEY-RECEIVER-001');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.amount).to.eql(100);",
                  "  pm.expect(body.participantId).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('participantId'));",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', body.id);",
                  "  console.log('transactionId set to', body.id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Create — montant invalide (< 0.01)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"senderKey\": \"KEY-SENDER-001\",\n  \"receiverKey\": \"KEY-RECEIVER-001\",\n  \"amount\": -5.00,\n  \"participantId\": \"{{participantId}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 — montant invalide', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Create — receiverKey manquant",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"senderKey\": \"KEY-SENDER-001\",\n  \"amount\": 50.00,\n  \"participantId\": \"{{participantId}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 — champ manquant', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Create — senderKey vide",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"senderKey\": \"\",\n  \"receiverKey\": \"KEY-RECEIVER-001\",\n  \"amount\": 50.00,\n  \"participantId\": \"{{participantId}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 — senderKey blank', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Create — participantId manquant",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"senderKey\": \"KEY-SENDER-001\",\n  \"receiverKey\": \"KEY-RECEIVER-001\",\n  \"amount\": 50.00\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 — participantId manquant', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET All Transactions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is array', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array');",
                  "  if (body.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', body[0].id);",
                  "    pm.test('Champs attendus présents', () => {",
                  "      pm.expect(body[0]).to.include.all.keys(",
                  "        'id','senderKey','receiverKey','amount','participantId','status','createdAt'",
                  "      );",
                  "    });",
                  "  }",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Transaction by ID",
          "description": "Utilise {{transactionId}} défini par POST Create ou Saga Simulation.",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions/{{transactionId}}"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('transactionId')) {",
                  "  console.warn('transactionId vide — lancez POST Create ou Saga Simulation en premier');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Champs attendus présents', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.include.all.keys(",
                  "    'id','senderKey','receiverKey','amount','participantId','status','createdAt','updatedAt'",
                  "  );",
                  "  pm.expect(body.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('transactionId'));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Transaction by ID — 404",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 404', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Réconciliation (UC08)",
      "description": "Filtre les transactions par participantId et plage de dates.\nHeader X-Participant-Id obligatoire.\nParams : startDate et endDate au format ISO-8601 (ex: 2026-01-01T00:00:00).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Réconciliation — plage valide",
          "description": "Retourne les transactions du participant sur les 24 dernières heures.",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Participant-Id", "value": "{{participantId}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions/reconciliation?startDate=2026-01-01T00:00:00&endDate=2099-12-31T23:59:59",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v2", "transactions", "reconciliation"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "startDate", "value": "2026-01-01T00:00:00" },
                { "key": "endDate",   "value": "2099-12-31T23:59:59" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Réponse est un tableau', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Toutes les transactions appartiennent au participant', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  const pid = pm.collectionVariables.get('participantId');",
                  "  body.forEach(tx => pm.expect(tx.participantId).to.eql(pid));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Réconciliation — header X-Participant-Id manquant",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions/reconciliation?startDate=2026-01-01T00:00:00&endDate=2099-12-31T23:59:59",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v2", "transactions", "reconciliation"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "startDate", "value": "2026-01-01T00:00:00" },
                { "key": "endDate",   "value": "2099-12-31T23:59:59" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 — header manquant', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Réconciliation — participant sans transactions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Participant-Id", "value": "PART-INEXISTANT-999" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v2/transactions/reconciliation?startDate=2026-01-01T00:00:00&endDate=2099-12-31T23:59:59",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v2", "transactions", "reconciliation"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "startDate", "value": "2026-01-01T00:00:00" },
                { "key": "endDate",   "value": "2099-12-31T23:59:59" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 — tableau vide', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Tableau vide', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array').that.is.empty;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
